    <fr:title text="{P}_m (R)">
      <fr:tex display="inline">\mathcal {P}_m (R)</fr:tex>
    </fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
    <fr:authors></fr:authors>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>The set of all polynomials of degree at most <fr:tex display="inline">m</fr:tex> with coefficients in ring <fr:tex display="inline">R</fr:tex> is denoted by <fr:tex display="inline">\mathcal {P}_m (R)</fr:tex>.
    In other words,
    <fr:tex display="block">         \mathcal {P}_m (R) = \set { p \in  \mathcal {P}(R) | \deg (p) \leq  m}     </fr:tex>
    where <fr:tex display="inline">\mathcal {P}(R)</fr:tex> is the <fr:link type="local" href="def-0027.xml" addr="def-0027" title="Polynomial">set of all polynomials</fr:link> with coefficients in <fr:tex display="inline">R</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:backmatter>
